  m_Name: GameHelper_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 1899bf3d1cd7c7c4f9e00659963ab3f8, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items: []
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 956792377147392
    m_Localized: Interface-Quest
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 956832365641728
    m_Localized: "The main mission is to reach the destination, but in some cases,
      you may be required to collect certain items. \r\nThe items to be collected
      will appear in the top left; if collected, they will have a green outline,
      otherwise red.\r"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957132510035968
    m_Localized: Interface-Items
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957139527106560
    m_Localized: "At the bottom center, there is the item bar. \r\nEach item has
      its own number of remaining uses indicated at the bottom; if it is not indicated,
      it means that the number of uses is infinite.\r\nSome items need to be equipped
      before they can be used; such equippable items will have a red outline if not
      equipped, otherwise green."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957339645739008
    m_Localized: Interface-Minimap
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957342195875840
    m_Localized: "At the top right, you will find the minimap. \r\nThis minimap is
      created thanks to the capabilities of the TXRU model and is able to provide
      various useful information and filter out the useless ones. \r\nAmong the most
      important information are the environment around you, your position, the position
      of enemies, and their field of vision. \r\nThrough this, you can estimate when
      you enter their visual range, but be careful: the indicator of your position
      does not indicate the space you occupy. \r\nOther useful information includes
      items you can collect/use, the destination, and passages."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957514200088576
    m_Localized: The jump
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957516649562112
    m_Localized: "This is not a common jump; in fact, thanks to the special characteristics
      of the TXRU, it creates a significant impact. \r\nYou can use the jump to generate
      a loud noise with the purpose of distracting the guards."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957688314036224
    m_Localized: The Checkpoint
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957691300380672
    m_Localized: "This strange portal allows you to save a moment in time and return
      to it later, but be careful: this tool is not perfect because it generates
      temporal distortions. \r\nAfter the first use, it will take you forward in
      time by 1 second every time!"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957823605506048
    m_Localized: Box A
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 957826558296064
    m_Localized: "By using the materials from this common metal box, you are able
      to change shape and transform into a box. \r\nBy becoming a box, you could
      go unnoticed, but be careful: the guards won't hesitate to destroy you if you
      disturb their work! \r\nMoreover, the transformation into a box has its drawbacks:
      it prevents you from using your other abilities and/or tools, but you can always
      return to your original form."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 958117076762624
    m_Localized: Laser Gun
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 958119320715264
    m_Localized: "By merging with this weapon, you are able to shoot lasers. \r\nTo
      merge with the weapon, you must first equip it. Once equipped, you can shoot.
      \r\nBe careful: the impact of the shot will prevent you from moving for a moment."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 958258001182720
    m_Localized: Invisibility device
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 958261092384768
    m_Localized: By connecting this device to your body, you can become invisible,
      but the invisibility has a very limited duration!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds: []
